        <h3 class="mt-4">For Bachelorette Party Supplies & Novelties</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Two Cumberland:</strong> Party favors, cheeky apparel, decorations — perfect for your weekend vibe.</li>
          <li><strong>Candy Shops (Market Street Sweets):</strong> Add Charleston-themed candies or novelty sweets to your festivities.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="mt-4">For Stylish Clothing & Accessories</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>King Street Boutiques:</strong> Trendy dresses, swimwear, accessories at Hampden Clothing, Copper Penny, and more.</li>
          <li><strong>The Tiny Tassel:</strong> Colorful earrings, gifts, and private shopping for groups.</li>
          <li><strong>Local Designer Shops:</strong> Proud Mary Global Textiles and other unique Charleston-made finds.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="mt-4">For Unique Gifts & Souvenirs</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Grit & Grace:</strong> Oyster shell jewelry dishes, handmade gifts, and permanent jewelry experiences.</li>
          <li><strong>Charleston Candle Co.:</strong> Locally-made candles inspired by Charleston’s charm, plus candle-making classes.</li>
          <li><strong>A Maker’s Post:</strong> Curated handmade goods by local artisans — perfect souvenirs.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="mt-4">For a Fun & Unique Experience</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Tijon Fragrance Lab:</strong> Create custom perfumes in private classes — a unique group activity.</li>
          <li><strong>Southern Ruetz Hat Bar:</strong> Make your own custom hats with bubbly on the side for a truly memorable day.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="mt-5">Tips for Shopping with a Bachelorette Group:</h4>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Stick Together (Mostly):</strong> Decide whether to browse as a group or split up and meet later.</li>
          <li><strong>Have a Budget in Mind:</strong> Avoid overspending and keep the fun stress-free.</li>
          <li><strong>Consider Group Outfits/Accessories:</strong> Matching accessories or themed looks are great for photos.</li>
          <li><strong>Don’t Forget Souvenirs:</strong> Bring home something to remember the trip by!</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="mt-4">While we can’t show store interiors here, we recommend checking out these shops on Instagram or their websites for the latest vibes. Happy shopping!</p>

        <p>Looking for other ideas? Visit our Charleston bachelorette ideas page.</p>

        <hr class="my-5">

        <h2 class="mt-5">The Ultimate Walkable Bachelorette Party Guide</h2>
        <p>When planning a bachelorette bash, choosing a walkable location can elevate the entire experience. It allows for spontaneous adventures, easy transitions between venues, and a more connected and social atmosphere for the bride tribe. Here are some top-notch walkable areas ideal for a bachelorette getaway, keeping in mind a mix of daytime delights and nighttime fun:</p>

        <h4 class="mt-4">1. Downtown Charleston, South Carolina (USA): The Classic Choice</h4>
        <p><strong>Why it's amazing for a walkable bachelorette:</strong> Charleston's historic downtown peninsula is incredibly pedestrian-friendly and packed with charm. You can wander through cobblestone streets, admire stunning architecture, and stumble upon hidden courtyards. Everything is relatively close, making it easy to hop from a spa appointment to a rooftop bar to a delicious dinner, all on foot.</p>

        <h5 class="mt-3">Key Walkable Neighborhoods within Downtown:</h5>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>The French Quarter:</strong> Art galleries, boutique shops, waterfront views, great dining, and hidden gems.</li>
          <li><strong>Market Street Area:</strong> City Market, people-watching, and lively energy with souvenir shops and eateries.</li>
          <li><strong>Upper King Street:</strong> Trendy nightlife, bars, live music, and late-night fun.
          </li>
          <li><strong>Lower King Street:</strong> Upscale boutiques, fine dining, and a more sophisticated shopping vibe.</li>
          <li><strong>South of Broad:</strong> Gorgeous historic homes, gardens, and photo-perfect strolls at a relaxed pace.</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="mt-3"><strong>Bachelorette Perks:</strong> Spas, rooftop bars with views (The Vendue, Stars Rooftop), carriage tours, ghost tours, Michael At Your Place Charleston, and endless dining options. The perfect setup for day-to-night bachelorette magic on foot!</p>

